TextSection.Contents: Supratip dysplasia is a rare, congenital, non-syndromic, nose and cavum malformation characterized by the presence of a bulbous, soft tissue hypertrophy located in the middle-to-distal third of the nasal dorsum, in association with deformed, slightly laterally- and caudally-placed nasal alae and a scar-like atrophic skin lesion located at the nasal tip. Respiratory function is not affected.
